title: El Paso reallocating COVID-19 vaccines meant for community clinics elsewhere
author: Adriana Candelaria
description: Health leaders in the city of El Paso are re-distributing COVID-19 vaccines originally allocated for community clinics. According to information from the Texas Department of State Health Services, community clinics are receiving COVID-19 vaccines each week. Caption: Adriana Candelaria reports on why the city of El Paso is reallocating COVID-19 vaccines meant for community clinics. (KFOX14)
